devdoc.details: The provider acts as the central hub for all ProviderContracts.    It stores the addresses for all contracts so when one contract wants to    communicate with with another, it must go:      Calling Contract -> AddressProvider -> Destination Contract    It also serves as a communication hub and a version manager that can    upgrade existing contracts and remove contractsfor simplicity, this is the only contract that does not have de-coupled storage

addContract(bytes32,address).details: addContract does two things:      1.) registers the address of given ProviderContract in the registry      2.) sets the registry address in given ProviderContract so only          the registry can call functions on given contract

params.owner: The owner address of this contract.

returns.contractAddr: - address of contract registered under given provider key

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

removeContract(bytes32).details: removes contract address registered under given provider key

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

params._newAddress: - new contract address to register under given key

addressStorage.details: addressStorage mapping allows efficient lookup of current contract version     	addressStorageHistory maintains record of all contract versions

devdoc.title: Central hub for ProvidersContracts that stores all contract addresses    and facilitates inter-contract communication

getContract(bytes32).notice: returns contract address registered under given provider key

getContract(bytes32,uint256).notice: overloaded getContract to return explicit version of contract

upgradeContract(bytes32,address).notice: replaces contract address registered under given key with provided address
